    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it wasn't just a coincidence. it was a specific resonance. i could feel the vibration in my chest and the air just... went still. and i'm not talking about a breeze, i'm talking about the actual weight of the air changing. i know physics says it's impossible, but i've felt it. if you look at the math of resonance frequencies, there has to be a way for a specific hertz to interact with a pressure gradient. just help me figure out the math of what that frequency might be, even theoretically.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
